        "content": "### The Lifecycle\n```\nCREATE (POST /v1/messages/batches)\n  ŌåÆ Submit up to 100,000 requests in one payload (max 256 MB)\n  \nPROCESS (automatic)\n  ŌåÆ Status: queued ŌåÆ processing ŌåÆ ended\n  ŌåÆ Individual requests: processing ŌåÆ succeeded | errored | canceled | expired\n  ŌåÆ Typical completion: < 1 hour (max 24 hours SLA)\n  \nRETRIEVE (GET /v1/messages/batches/{id}/results)\n  ŌåÆ JSONL stream of results matched by custom_id\n  ŌåÆ Results available for 29 days\n  \nCANCEL (POST /v1/messages/batches/{id}/cancel)\n  ŌåÆ Stops NEW processing, keeps already-completed results\n  ŌåÆ Status: canceling ŌåÆ ended (with partial results)\n```\n\n### Request Format\nEach request in the batch is a full Messages API call:\n```json\n{\n  \"requests\": [\n    {\n      \"custom_id\": \"classify-email-042\",\n      \"params\": {\n        \"model\": \"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\n        \"max_tokens\": 256,\n        \"system\": \"Classify this email as: urgent, normal, or spam.\",\n        \"messages\": [\n          {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"Subject: Meeting tomorrow...\"}\n        ]\n      }\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\nKey details:\n- **`custom_id`** is YOUR identifier ŌĆö use it to match results back to your data\n- **`params`** accepts everything the Messages API does: tools, system prompts, temperature, etc.\n- You can **mix models** in one batch ŌĆö Haiku for simple tasks, Sonnet for harder ones\n- Results come back in **no guaranteed order** ŌĆö always match on `custom_id`\n\n### Rate Limits (by tier)\n| Tier | RPM to Batch API | Max Requests in Queue |\n|------|-----------------|----------------------|\n| Tier 1 | 50 | 100,000 |\n| Tier 2 | 1,000 | 200,000 |\n| Tier 3 | 2,000 | 300,000 |\n| Tier 4 | 4,000 | 500,000 |"
