        "heading": "Background & Context",
        "content": "The default developer instinct is to use the most capable model for everything. It feels safer ŌĆö \"Opus won't mess this up.\" But this is the single biggest cost mistake in AI engineering.\n\nAnthropic's model lineup is explicitly designed for tiered routing. Haiku exists to handle the 60-70% of tasks that don't need reasoning. Sonnet handles the 25-35% that need quality code and analysis. Opus handles the 5-10% that genuinely require deep, multi-step reasoning.\n\nThe price spread is 5x between Haiku and Opus. For a production system doing 10K requests/day, routing correctly saves **$150+/day** ŌĆö before stacking caching or batching on top."
