        "content": "### Per-Request Cost Comparison\n```\nTask: Classify an email (500 input, 20 output tokens)\n  Haiku:  500 ├Ś $1/1M + 20 ├Ś $5/1M    = $0.0006\n  Sonnet: 500 ├Ś $3/1M + 20 ├Ś $15/1M   = $0.0018\n  Opus:   500 ├Ś $5/1M + 20 ├Ś $25/1M   = $0.0030\n  \n  Opus is 5x more expensive for the same classification.\n  At 10K emails/day: Haiku=$6, Sonnet=$18, Opus=$30\n\nTask: Generate a code function (1K input, 2K output tokens)\n  Haiku:  1K ├Ś $1 + 2K ├Ś $5    = $0.011\n  Sonnet: 1K ├Ś $3 + 2K ├Ś $15   = $0.033\n  Opus:   1K ├Ś $5 + 2K ├Ś $25   = $0.055\n  \n  Sonnet is the sweet spot ŌĆö quality code at 60% of Opus cost.\n```\n\n### Portfolio Routing Example\n```\nMonthly: 100K requests\n  Before (all Opus): 100K ├Ś avg $0.04 = $4,000/month\n\n  After (routed):\n    60K Haiku  (60%): 60K ├Ś $0.0008  = $48\n    35K Sonnet (35%): 35K ├Ś $0.025   = $875\n    5K Opus    (5%):  5K ├Ś $0.04     = $200\n    Total: $1,123/month\n\n  Savings: $2,877/month (72%)\n```\n\n### Output Tokens Dominate Cost\nA critical insight: **output tokens are 5x more expensive than input** across all models. Optimizing for shorter outputs often saves more than switching models.\n\n```\nOptimization: \"Respond in under 100 words\" vs. unconstrained\n  Opus unconstrained: 500 in + 2000 out = $0.0525\n  Opus constrained:   550 in + 200 out  = $0.0078\n  Savings: 85% ŌĆö just from shorter output!\n```"
