        "heading": "Real-World Patterns",
        "content": "### The \"Opus Plans, Sonnet Executes\" Pattern\nAlready in use in your lab-01 architecture:\n1. **Opus** creates the execution plan (high-level reasoning, 1 call)\n2. **Sonnet** executes each step (code generation, multiple calls)\n3. **Haiku** validates outputs (quick checks between steps)\n\nCost: ~$0.05 for planning + ~$0.03 ├Ś N steps + ~$0.001 ├Ś N validations\nvs. ~$0.05 ├Ś (N+1) if Opus did everything.\n\n### Support Ticket Routing\n```\nTier 1 ŌĆö Haiku: \"Is this a known issue?\" ŌåÆ Match against FAQ (80% resolved)\nTier 2 ŌĆö Sonnet: \"Draft a response\" ŌåÆ Generate custom reply (15% of volume)\nTier 3 ŌĆö Opus: \"Investigate root cause\" ŌåÆ Complex debugging (5% of volume)\n```\n\n### Content Pipeline\n```\nClassify content type ŌåÆ Haiku\nGenerate first draft ŌåÆ Sonnet\nReview for quality/accuracy ŌåÆ Sonnet\nHandle edge cases flagged by review ŌåÆ Opus\n```"
