        "heading": "Background & Context",
        "content": "Every time you send a request to Claude, the model processes your entire input from scratch ŌĆö system prompt, tool definitions, conversation history, all of it. For a 50K-token system prompt repeated across 100 requests, that's 5M tokens processed... 100 times.\n\nPrompt caching solves this by letting Anthropic store and reuse the computed representations of your input prefix. The model skips the \"prefill\" phase for cached content and jumps straight to generating the response. Result: **90% cheaper on cached tokens** and **13-31% faster TTFT**.\n\nThis is the highest-ROI optimization for any application that sends the same (or similar) content repeatedly ŌĆö chatbots, RAG systems, agentic loops, code review tools."
