        "heading": "How It Works ŌĆö Full Treatment",
        "content": "### Prefix-Based Caching\nThe cache operates on **ordered blocks** processed in this sequence:\n```\ntools ŌåÆ system ŌåÆ messages\n```\n\nYou place `cache_control` markers on blocks. Everything up to and including the marked block is cached as a single prefix. On the next request, if the prefix matches exactly, the cached computation is reused.\n\n```\nRequest 1 (CACHE WRITE):\n  ŌöīŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöÉ\n  Ōöé System prompt (10K tokens)  Ōöé ŌåÉ Processed & cached (1.25x cost)\n  Ōöé     cache_control: ephemeralŌöé\n  Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöż\n  Ōöé User message (200 tokens)   Ōöé ŌåÉ Processed normally (1x cost)\n  ŌööŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöś\n\nRequest 2 (CACHE READ):\n  ŌöīŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöÉ\n  Ōöé System prompt (10K tokens)  Ōöé ŌåÉ Served from cache (0.1x cost)\n  Ōöé     cache_control: ephemeralŌöé\n  Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöż\n  Ōöé User message (300 tokens)   Ōöé ŌåÉ Processed normally (1x cost)\n  ŌööŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöś\n```\n\n### Cache Invalidation Rules\nThe cache is **invalidated** (new entry written) when ANY of these change:\n- Tool definitions\n- Web search / citation toggles\n- Speed settings (e.g., fast mode toggle)\n- Images in the prompt\n- Thinking parameters (budget_tokens, etc.)\n- `tool_choice` parameter (invalidates message blocks only)\n\nThe cache stays **valid** when:\n- Only content AFTER the breakpoint changes (new user messages, different questions)\n- Request metadata changes (temperature, max_tokens ŌĆö these don't affect prefix)\n\n### Minimum Token Thresholds\n| Model | Minimum Cacheable Tokens |\n|-------|-------------------------|\n| Opus 4.6 | 4,096 |\n| Sonnet 4.6 | 2,048 |\n| Haiku 4.5 | 2,048 |\n\nBelow the minimum? The request processes normally ŌĆö no error, just no caching. Check `usage.cache_creation_input_tokens` in the response to verify.\n\n### TTL Behavior\n| Duration | Cost Multiplier | Use Case |\n|----------|----------------|----------|\n| 5 min (default) | 1.25x write | High-frequency: chatbots, agentic loops |\n| 1 hour (explicit) | 2.0x write | Lower-frequency: RAG, periodic queries |\n\n**Important**: TTL is an absolute clock from initial write. Cache hits do NOT extend the TTL. A hit at 4:59 still expires at 5:00.\n\n### Max Breakpoints\nYou can place up to **4 explicit `cache_control` blocks** per request. Design your prefix layers carefully."
