        "heading": "Code Walkthrough",
        "content": "### Pattern 1: Auto-Caching (Simplest)\n```python\nfrom anthropic import Anthropic\n\nclient = Anthropic()\n\n# Single cache_control at request level ŌĆö system manages breakpoint placement\nresponse = client.messages.create(\n    model=\"claude-sonnet-4-6-20250514\",\n    max_tokens=1024,\n    cache_control={\"type\": \"ephemeral\"},\n    system=\"You are an expert Python developer. You follow PEP 8, write type hints, and prefer composition over inheritance...\",\n    messages=[\n        {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"How do I implement a retry decorator?\"}\n    ]\n)\n\n# Verify caching is active\nu = response.usage\nprint(f\"Cache written: {u.cache_creation_input_tokens} tokens\")\nprint(f\"Cache read:    {u.cache_read_input_tokens} tokens\")\nprint(f\"Uncached:      {u.input_tokens} tokens\")\n```\n\n### Pattern 2: Explicit Breakpoints (RAG / Large Context)\n```python\nresponse = client.messages.create(\n    model=\"claude-sonnet-4-6-20250514\",\n    max_tokens=2048,\n    system=[\n        {\n            \"type\": \"text\",\n            \"text\": \"You are a document analysis assistant. Answer using ONLY the provided context.\",\n            \"cache_control\": {\"type\": \"ephemeral\"}  # Breakpoint 1: instructions\n        },\n        {\n            \"type\": \"text\",\n            \"text\": load_knowledge_base(),  # 50K tokens of documents\n            \"cache_control\": {\"type\": \"ephemeral\"}  # Breakpoint 2: documents\n        }\n    ],\n    messages=[\n        {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"What are the key compliance requirements?\"}\n    ]\n)\n\n# First request: writes cache (50K ├Ś 1.25x = 62.5K token cost)\n# Subsequent: reads cache (50K ├Ś 0.1x = 5K token cost) ŌĆö 90% savings\n```\n\n### Pattern 3: 1-Hour TTL (Lower Frequency)\n```python\nresponse = client.messages.create(\n    model=\"claude-sonnet-4-6-20250514\",\n    max_tokens=1024,\n    cache_control={\"type\": \"ephemeral\", \"ttl\": \"1h\"},\n    system=\"...\",\n    messages=[...]\n)\n# 2x write cost, but cache persists for 1 hour instead of 5 minutes\n# Break-even: 2 cache reads (vs 1 read for 5-min cache)\n```\n\n### Pattern 4: Multi-Turn Conversation\n```python\nconversation = []\n\ndef chat(user_message: str) -> str:\n    conversation.append({\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": user_message})\n    \n    response = client.messages.create(\n        model=\"claude-sonnet-4-6-20250514\",\n        max_tokens=1024,\n        cache_control={\"type\": \"ephemeral\"},  # Auto-caches growing history\n        system=\"You are a helpful coding assistant.\",\n        messages=conversation\n    )\n    \n    reply = response.content[0].text\n    conversation.append({\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": reply})\n    \n    u = response.usage\n    cached_pct = u.cache_read_input_tokens / max(u.cache_read_input_tokens + u.input_tokens, 1) * 100\n    print(f\"Cache hit: {cached_pct:.0f}% of input tokens\")\n    \n    return reply\n\n# Turn 1: Full processing (cache write)\nchat(\"What's a good pattern for database connection pooling?\")\n\n# Turn 2: System + turn 1 cached, only new message processed\nchat(\"Can you show me the async version?\")\n\n# Turn 3: System + turns 1-2 cached\nchat(\"How would I add health checks to that pool?\")\n```\n\n### Pattern 5: Agentic Loop with Tool Caching\n```python\ntools = [\n    {\"name\": \"search\", \"description\": \"...\", \"input_schema\": {...}},\n    {\"name\": \"calculate\", \"description\": \"...\", \"input_schema\": {...}},\n    # ... 20 tools = ~5K tokens of definitions\n]\n\nmessages = [{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"Research and analyze...\"}]\n\nwhile True:\n    response = client.messages.create(\n        model=\"claude-sonnet-4-6-20250514\",\n        max_tokens=4096,\n        cache_control={\"type\": \"ephemeral\"},\n        system=\"You are an autonomous research agent.\",\n        tools=tools,  # Cached across every iteration\n        messages=messages\n    )\n    \n    if response.stop_reason == \"tool_use\":\n        # Execute tools, add results to messages\n        messages.append({\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": response.content})\n        tool_results = execute_tools(response.content)\n        messages.append({\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": tool_results})\n    else:\n        break  # Final response\n\n# Each loop iteration: tools + system + prior messages all cached\n# Only the NEW tool results are processed fresh\n```\n\n### Pattern 6: Streaming + Caching (Combined)\n```python\nwith client.messages.stream(\n    model=\"claude-sonnet-4-6-20250514\",\n    max_tokens=2048,\n    cache_control={\"type\": \"ephemeral\"},\n    system=\"Your large system prompt...\",\n    messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"Explain...\"}]\n) as stream:\n    for text in stream.text_stream:\n        print(text, end=\"\", flush=True)\n    \n    # Cache stats available after stream completes\n    msg = stream.get_final_message()\n    print(f\"\\nCache read: {msg.usage.cache_read_input_tokens} tokens\")\n```"
