        "heading": "Common Mistakes & Gotchas",
        "content": "### 1. Putting dynamic content before static content\n```python\n# BAD ŌĆö timestamp changes every request, cache never hits\nsystem=[\n    {\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": f\"Time: {datetime.now()}\", \"cache_control\": {\"type\": \"ephemeral\"}},\n    {\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"Your stable 50K prompt...\"}  # Never cached!\n]\n\n# GOOD ŌĆö stable content first, dynamic content last (after breakpoint)\nsystem=[\n    {\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"Your stable 50K prompt...\", \"cache_control\": {\"type\": \"ephemeral\"}},\n    {\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": f\"Current time: {datetime.now()}\"}  # Not cached, that's fine\n]\n```\n\n### 2. Not checking if cache is actually working\n```python\n# ALWAYS verify cache activation in development\nresponse = client.messages.create(...)\nu = response.usage\n\nif u.cache_creation_input_tokens == 0 and u.cache_read_input_tokens == 0:\n    print(\"WARNING: Caching not active! Check minimum token threshold and prefix stability.\")\n```\n\n### 3. Changing tool_choice between requests\n```python\n# BAD ŌĆö tool_choice change invalidates message cache\nresp1 = client.messages.create(tool_choice=\"auto\", cache_control=..., ...)\nresp2 = client.messages.create(tool_choice=\"any\", cache_control=..., ...)  # Cache miss!\n\n# GOOD ŌĆö keep tool_choice consistent across requests\n```\n\n### 4. Expecting batch API cache hits\nCache hits in batches are **best-effort** (30-98% hit rate). Requests may process on different machines. For guaranteed savings, use caching with real-time API where you control request timing.\n\n### 5. Exceeding 4 breakpoints\nMax 4 `cache_control` blocks per request. If you need more layers, consolidate your stable content into fewer blocks.\n\n### 6. Prefix below minimum threshold\nIf your cacheable content is under 2,048 tokens (Sonnet/Haiku) or 4,096 tokens (Opus), caching silently does nothing. Pad your system prompt with useful context if it's close to the threshold."
